cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily focused on the problem of face detection in images and video streams, which is a classic problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). 

The paper proposes a new solution based on compact convolutional neural networks cascade, which involves the use of machine learning techniques. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

The paper also discusses the implementation of the proposed detector using SSE/AVX/AVX2 instruction sets for Intel CPUs, Nvidia CUDA, and OpenCL, which suggests that it may be relevant to the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia). 

Finally, the paper emphasizes the high computational efficiency of the proposed detector, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
